                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d605">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/3321: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moore</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-04-11T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 11, 1929—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>44. Your 55, March 31, 4 p.m., eighth paragraph. In your discretion you may
                    communicate the following orally and confidentially to President Leguia. When
                    the time comes, President Hoover is ready to make a suggestion of settlement to
                    both Peru and Chile on the condition that the settlement which the President is
                    to suggest has the prior approval of both Peru and Chile.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
